develop-glad-reef, develop-swift-pine, develop-keen-dale, develop-grand-oak, develop-glad-vale_\n    75→\n    76→- **[lesson-20260306-005]** (prompt_improvement, confidence: high) The fix.md prompt is still corrupted after at least 3 evolution cycles — it contains meta-conversation text asking for write permissions instead of actual fix instructions. The evolution process has identified this problem repeatedly but has been unable to correct it due to file write permission constraints.\n    77→  _Action: Replace the entire contents of fix.md with: '# Fix Validation Failures\\n\\nThe previous validation step failed. Your job is to fix the code so validation passes.\\n\\n## Validation Output\\n{{validation_output}}\\n\\n## Rules\\n1. Analyze the root cause before editing any code\\n2. Run the failing test in isolation first to confirm reproduction\\n3. Make minimal, targeted changes — only touch code directly related to the failure\\n4. If a previous fix attempt is visible in the diff, try a fundamentally different approach\\n5. After applying your fix, run the exact failing test command and confirm it passes before reporting success. If it still fails, report fail immediately'_\n    78→  _Evidence: develop-light-drift_\n    79→\n    80→- **[lesson-20260306-006]** (prompt_improvement, confidence: high) The update-docs.md prompt is still corrupted after at least 3 evolution cycles — it contains meta-conversation text asking for write permissions instead of actual documentation update instructions. The evolution process has identified this problem repeatedly but has been unable to correct it.\n    81→  _Action: Replace the entire contents of update-docs.md with: '# Update Documentation\\n\\nCompare the current source code against project documentation and update docs to reflect reality.\\n\\n## Process\\n1. Read the source code changes from the current implementation\\n2. Grep for specific strings, flags, and config keys in source\\n3. Compare against existing documentation\\n4. Edit only the sections that are actually out of date\\n5. Re-read each file after editing to confirm it is valid\\n\\n## Rules\\n- If no documentation changes are needed, report success immediately\\n- Only report fail if an actual write to a doc file failed\\n- Do not invent behavior not present in source code\\n- If the drift is large, update only sections affected by the current change rather than reconciling everything\\n- Spend no more than a few minutes on comparison'_\n    82→  _Evidence: develop-light-drift_\n    83→\n    84→- **[lesson-20260306-008]** (new_step, confidence: high) Four steps remain orphaned in the workflow: check-vet-build-steps, check-vet-build-wiring, check-preflight, and check-orphaned-steps. They have step definitions and edges from their own results but no incoming edges from other steps, so they never execute. These were added by previous evolution cycles but never wired into the main flow.\n    85→  _Action: Wire check-vet-build-steps between test:success and update-docs: change 'test:success -> update-docs' to 'test:success -> check-vet-build-steps', add 'check-vet-build-steps:success -> update-docs' and 'check-vet-build-steps:fail -> fix'. Remove check-vet-build-wiring, check-preflight, and check-orphaned-steps as they are redundant meta-validation steps that should not be part of the production workflow — their concerns should be addressed by the evolution process itself, not by in-workflow script steps._\n    86→  _Evidence: develop-light-drift_\n    87→\n    88→- **[lesson-20260306-007]** (new_step, confidence: high) 27 out of 28 total runs with zero step results recorded (adding 10 new: develop-firm-lark, develop-vivid-brook, develop-quiet-vale, develop-warm-hare, develop-bold-elm, develop-bright-hawk, develop-deft-elm, develop-light-cove, develop-cool-vale, develop-proud-reef). Every run continues to fail before executing any step. This is now overwhelmingly the dominant failure mode — no workflow-level improvement can