ence: high) The update-docs.md prompt is still corrupted — it contains meta-conversation text asking for write permissions instead of actual documentation update instructions. This has persisted for 5+ evolution cycles without being corrected.\n    97→  _Action: Replace the entire contents of update-docs.md with the intended prompt: instructions to compare source code against documentation, grep for specific strings/flags, only report fail if a write failed, time-bounding rule for large drifts, and self-check instruction to re-read after editing._\n    98→  _Evidence: develop-light-drift_\n    99→\n   100→- **[lesson-20260306-009]** (new_step, confidence: medium) The workflow definition contains a duplicate 'check-preflight' step (defined twice with identical content) and four orphaned steps (check-vet-build-steps, check-vet-build-wiring, check-preflight, check-orphaned-steps) that are never reached from the main flow. The duplicate step name may cause parser errors or undefined behavior, potentially contributing to the universal startup failures."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WJ3dv2tt3U5N3cEvcAex23","session_id":"016a7e3e-d9d2-46f5-8da9-2b20f96020ee","uuid":"0984a807-4eee-4b26-bf91-1489859aadf0"}
