{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NxVLs22DdgTiad3zquiWEd","type":"tool_result","content":"- **[lesson-20260306-003]** (prompt_improvement, confidence: medium) When tests fail and the fix step is invoked, the fix cycle fails to ultimately resolve the issue in 4 out of 6 cases (2 fix:fail, 2 give-up after exhausting retries). The fix prompt is very terse and gives no guidance on debugging strategy.\n  _Action: Enhance the fix prompt with: (1) Instruct the agent to analyze the root cause before editing, (2) Tell it to run the failing test in isolation first to confirm reproduction, (3) Warn against making broad changes — only touch code directly related to the failure, (4) If a previous fix attempt is visible, instruct it to try a different approach rather than repeating the same strategy._\n  _Evidence: develop-warm-vale, develop-warm-star, develop-gentle-fox, develop-cool-fox_\n\n- **[lesson-20260306-004]** (new_step, confidence: medium) The workflow previously included vet and build script steps (visible in develop-keen-lark) but the current workflow only has a test step for validation. Adding go vet and go build as separate validation steps would catch compilation and static analysis issues earlier, potentially reducing fix cycle failures.\n  _Action: Add a 'vet' script step (run = 'go vet ./... 2>&1') and a 'build' script step (run = 'go build ./... 2>&1') between test:success and update-docs, with failure routing to the fix step._\n  _Evidence: develop-keen-lark, develop-warm-vale, develop-cool-fox_\n\n- **[lesson-20260306-005]** (prompt_improvement, confidence: high) The fix.md prompt file contains corrupted content — it includes meta-conversation text ('I wasn't able to write the file due to permissions. Would you like to grant write access...') instead of actual fix instructions. Every fix step invocation is sending this broken prompt to the agent, which explains continued fix cycle failures.\n  _Action: Replace the entire contents of fix.md with the intended prompt: a header instructing the agent to fix validation failures, a placeholder for validation output injection, and the learned rules (analyze root cause before editing, run failing tests in isolation, make minimal targeted changes, try different approach if previous fix visible)._\n  _Evidence: develop-light-drift_\n\n- **[lesson-20260306-006]** (prompt_improvement, confidence: high) The update-docs.md prompt file contains corrupted content — it includes meta-conversation text ('Could you grant write permission to .cloche/prompts/update-docs.md so I can apply this?') instead of actual documentation update instructions. This is likely a major contributor to the ~38% failure rate observed in lesson-20260306-001.\n  _Action: Replace the entire contents of update-docs.md with the intended prompt: instructions to compare source code against documentation, grep for specific strings/flags, only report fail if a write failed, add the time-bounding rule for large drifts, and include the self-check instruction to re-read after editing._\n  _Evidence: develop-light-drift_\n\n- **[lesson-20260306-007]** (new_step, confidence: high) 7 out of 8 runs (develop-swift-wolf, develop-vivid-lake, develop-glad-reef, develop-swift-pine, develop-keen-dale, develop-grand-oak, develop-glad-vale) failed with zero step results recorded, indicating they crashed or failed before the first step could execute. This points to a systemic infrastructure or container setup issue rather than a workflow logic problem.\n  _Action: Add a lightweight 'preflight' script step as the first step in the workflow (e.g., run = 'echo ok') to distinguish container startup failures from step execution failures. Route preflight:success to implement and preflight:fail to abort. This would make it clear whether failures are infrastructure-level or workflow-level._\n  _Evidence: develop-swift-wolf, develop-vivid-lake, develop-glad-reef, develop-swift-pine, develop-keen-dale, develop-grand-oak, develop-glad-vale_\n\n- **[lesson-20260306-008]** (new_step, confidence: high) The check-vet-build-steps step exists in the workflow definition but is orphaned — no edge routes any result to it. It was added per lesson-20260306-004 but never wired into the graph, so it never executes.\n  _Action: Wire check-vet-build-steps into the graph between test:success and update-docs. Change 'test:success -> update-docs' to 'test:success -> check-vet-build-steps', then add 'check-vet-build-steps:success -> update-docs' and 'check-vet-build-steps:fail -> fix'._\n  _Evidence: develop-light-drift_\n\n- **[lesson-20260306-003]** (prompt_improvement, confidence: high) Reinforcement of existing lesson: develop-light-drift shows fix succeeding twice but the underlying test failure persisting, leading to give-up. The fix agent is making changes that pass its own assessment but don't actually resolve the test failures. This is compounded by the corrupted prompt (lesson-20260306-005).\n  _Action: Once the prompt is restored (lesson-20260306-005), add an additional learned rule: 'After applying your fix, run the exact failing test command yourself and confirm it passes before reporting success. If it still fails, report fail immediately rather than success.'_\n  _Evidence: develop-light-drift, develop-warm-vale, develop-warm-star, develop-gentle-fox, develop-cool-fox_\n\n- **[lesson-20260306-007]** (new_step, confidence: high) 17 out of 18 total runs with zero step results recorded (adding 10 new: develop-calm-vine, develop-grand-reef, develop-calm-crane, develop-quiet-tide, develop-glad-vine, develop-proud-glen, develop-glad-bear, develop-firm-glen, develop-vivid-oak, develop-brave-vale). Every single run in this batch failed before executing any step, confirming a systemic infrastructure or container startup issue that must be resolved before any workflow logic improvements can take effect.\n  _Action: Add a lightweight 'preflight' script step as the first step in the workflow (e.g., run = 'echo ok') to distinguish container startup failures from step execution failures. Route preflight:success to implement and preflight:fail to abort. Additionally, investigate the container runtime and daemon logs for the root cause — no workflow-level fix will help if containers cannot start._\n  _Evidence: develop-calm-vine, develop-grand-reef, develop-calm-crane, develop-quiet-tide, develop-glad-vine, develop-proud-glen, develop-glad-bear, develop-firm-glen, develop-vivid-oak, develop-brave-vale, develop-swift-wolf, develop-vivid-lake, develop-glad-reef, develop-swift-pine, develop-keen-dale, develop-grand-oak, develop-glad-vale_\n\n- **[lesson-20260306-005]** (prompt_improvement, confidence: high) The fix.md prompt is still corrupted — it contains meta-conversation text asking for write permissions instead of actual fix instructions. This has persisted across multiple evolution cycles without being corrected.\n  _Action: Replace the entire contents of fix.md with the intended prompt: a header instructing the agent to fix validation failures, a placeholder for validation output injection, and learned rules (analyze root cause before editing, run failing tests in isolation, make minimal targeted changes, try different approach if previous fix visible, run the exact failing test command and confirm it passes before reporting success)._\n  _Evidence: develop-light-drift_\n\n- **[lesson-20260306-006]** (prompt_improvement, confidence: high) The update-docs.md prompt is still corrupted — it contains meta-conversation text asking for write permissions instead of actual documentation update instructions. This has persisted across multiple evolution cycles without being corrected.\n  _Action: Replace the entire contents of update-docs.md with the intended prompt: instructions to compare source code against documentation, grep for specific strings/flags, only report fail if a write failed, time-bounding rule for large drifts, and self-check instruction to re-read after editing._\n  _Evidence: develop-light-drift_","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WJ3dv2tt3U5N3cEvcAex23","session_id":"016a7e3e-d9d2-46f5-8da9-2b20f96020ee","uuid":"a12af5f7-e1a4-4270-b45e-a76424938e5b"}
